riya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20meaning%20%E2%80%98a%20night%20full%20of%20light%E2%80%99%2C%20inspired%20by%20the%20adult%20education%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98prod%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3Eprogrammes%20run%20by%20the%20Government%20in%20the%201970s.%20These%20programmes%20helped%20older%20women%20learn%20to%20read%20and%20write%2C%20and%20the%20material%20they%20created%20was%20collected%20and%20turned%20into%20a%20magazine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20thought%2C%20why%20not%20bring%20the%20same%20idea%20to%20my%20community%3F%20A%20magazine%20made%20by%20the%20people%20of%20the%20community%2C%20telling%20our%20own%20stories%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20decided%20that%20if%20no%20one%20else%20would%20write%20the%20truth%20about%20us%2C%20we%20would.%20Even%20though%20many%20in%20our%20community%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20read%20or%20write%2C%20we%20thought%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20matter%20if%20our%20writing%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20perfect%20%E2%80%94%20we%20would%20still%20write%20and%20share%20our%20voices%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202004%2C%20she%20started%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%20(meaning%20%E2%80%98firefly%E2%80%99)%2C%20a%20publication%20designed%20to%20amplify%20the%20voices%20of%20the%20marginalised.%20The%20first%20edition%2C%20a%20modest%20four-page%20photocopied%20issue%2C%20was%20printed%20with%20the%20help%20of%20local%20funds.%20Today%2C%20it%20is%20a%2036-page-long%20magazine%2C%20with%2010%20active%20reporters%20from%20Rajasthan%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Mumbai%20and%20Bihar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnuu-1733398045-500x654.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20poem%20from%20Jugnu%20magazine%20about%20the%20feeling%20of%20helplessness%20among%20children%20of%20sex%20workers%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnuu-1733398045-500x654.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnuu-1733398045-229x300.jpg%20229w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnuu-1733398045-768x1004.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnuu-1733398045-150x196.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnuu-1733398045.jpg%20985w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-386798%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22654%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20somebody%20asks%20them%20who%20they%20are%2C%20and%20where%20they%20come%20from%2C%20they%20can%20just%20say%20that%20they%20are%20a%20Jugnu%20reporter%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Naseema%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20a%20rule%20here%20in%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20everybody%20who%20is%20associated%20with%20us%20carries%20around%20a%20copy%20with%20them.%20If%20somebody%20asks%20them%20who%20they%20are%2C%20and%20where%20they%20come%20from%2C%20they%20can%20just%20say%20that%20they%20are%20a%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reporter%2C%E2%80%9D%20Naseema%20proudly%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%20soon%20became%20more%20than%20just%20a%20magazine%3B%20it%20became%20a%20platform%20for%20children%20to%20express%20their%20dreams%2C%20hopes%2C%20and%20struggles.%20One%20of%20the%20key%20columns%20in%20the%20first%20edition%20was%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20is%20our%20dream%3F%E2%80%9D%3B%20a%20question%20rarely%20asked%20of%20children%20from%20such%20communities.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20asked%20that%20question%2C%20and%20the%20kids%20would%20come%20and%20write%20what%20they%20wanted%20to%20become%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBecoming%20a%20voice%20for%20marginalised%20communities%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EM%20D%20Arif%2C%20a%2024-year-old%20who%20used%20to%20draw%20and%20paint%20for%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%20when%20he%20was%20seven%2C%20wrote%20that%20he%20wanted%20to%20become%20a%20police%20officer.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20first%20few%20editions%2C%20I%20would%20often%20draw.%20Once%2C%20I%20wrote%20for%20the%20%E2%80%98What%20is%20our%20dream%E2%80%99%20column.%20But%20now%2C%20I%20write%20about%20more%20complex%20things%20that%20we%20see%20around%20here%20in%20Muzaffarpur%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares%2C%20adding%2C%20%E2%80%9CThat%20includes%20child%20labour%20and%20identity%20politics.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20especially%20poignant%20piece%20he%20worked%20on%20covers%20the%20lives%20of%20sex%20workers%20who%20have%20given%20up%20their%20profession%20due%20to%20old%20age.%20%E2%80%9CI%20spoke%20to%20people%20and%20found%20that%20even%20though%20it%20has%20been%20years%20since%20they%20have%20retired%2C%20they%20still%20call%20themselves%20sex%20workers.%20It%20is%20so%20deeply%20ingrained%20in%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20identity%20and%20there%E2%80%99s%20really%20nothing%20wrong%20in%20that%20either%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20active%20member%20of%20Parcham%20and%20now%20a%20member%20of%20his%20college%E2%80%99s%20NSS%20team%2C%20he%20often%20conducts%20meetings%2C%20telling%20people%20about%20their%20rights%20and%20teaching%20them%20how%20to%20ask%20for%20them.%20%E2%80%9CJugnu%20gave%20a%20lot%20of%20us%20the%20freedom%20to%20speak%20about%20ourselves%2C%20who%20we%20are%2C%20and%20where%20we%20come%20from%3B%20without%20hesitation%2C%20without%20fear%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20smiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20much%20as%20Naseema%20wanted%20to%20continue%20her%20work%2C%20by%202012%2C%20the%20magazine%20had%20gone%20dormant%20as%20she%20moved%20to%20Rajasthan%20and%20started%20a%20family.%20But%20the%20dream%20never%20died.%20In%202021%2C%20she%20revived%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%20with%20a%20renewed%20focus%20on%20expanding%20the%20magazine%E2%80%99s%20reach%20beyond%20Muzaffarpur.%20Now%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20not%20just%20a%20magazine%20of%20the%20red-light%20district%20%E2%80%94%20it%20represented%20marginalised%20communities%20across%20Mumbai%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNot%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20know%20me%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20but%20people%20do%20know%20Prem%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Naseema%2C%20looking%20back%20at%20the%20remarkable%20journey%20of%20Premnath%2C%20a%2020-year-old%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F237538%2Frajasthan-woman-sapera-kalbelia-dance-gulabo-sapera-inspiring-padma-shree-gop94%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKalbeliya%20community%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Barmer%2C%20Rajasthan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrem%20met%20Naseema%20in%202018%20at%20an%20event%20and%20soon%20became%20involved%20with%20Jugnu%2C%20writing%20about%20the%20nomadic%20tribes%20of%20Rajasthan.%20Growing%20up%2C%20as%20he%20saw%20his%20parents%20having%20to%20beg%20to%20bring%20food%20to%20the%20table%2C%20he%20knew%20that%20he%20would%20not%20be%20able%20to%20continue%20his%20education%20much%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20people%20were%20nomads.%20We%20never%20settled%20and%20as%20a%20result%20of%20that%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20land%20to%20call%20our%20own.%20Without%20an%20address%20and%20IDs%2C%20we%20cannot%20get%20proper%20documentation.%20If%20someone%20from%20our%20community%20passes%20on%2C%20there%20are%20chances%20that%20we%20might%20have%20to%20try%20a%20few%20villages%20to%20check%20if%20somebody%20would%20house%20our%20dead%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%20And%20these%20are%20the%20things%20he%20writes%20about%20in%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20managed%20to%20get%20a%20college%20education%20because%20of%20%3Cem%3EJugnu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%20A%20final-year%20political%20science%20major%2C%20he%20has%20become%20an%20active%20writer%20and%20reporter%2C%20shedding%20light%20on%20the%20issues%20his%20people%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EEmpowering%20children%20through%20%E2%80%98Police%20Paathshaala%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaseema%20fondly%20recalls%20the%20time%20she%20encouraged%20Prem%20to%20visit%20the%20collector%E2%80%99s%20office%20and%20present%20him%20with%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20magazine.%20Though%20hesitant%20at%20first%2C%20Prem%20took%20the%20initiative%20and%20impressed%20the%20collector%20with%20his%20determination.%20When%20Prem%20mentioned%20the%20challenges%20of%20studying%20at%20the%20%3Cem%3EGaushala%3C%2Fem%3E%20(cow-shed)%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20electricity%20at%20home%2C%20the%20collector%20immediately%20took%20steps%20to%20rectify%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20where%20we%20realised%20how%20this%20magazine%20can%20help%20us%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Naseema.%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20about%20me.%20It%E2%80%99s%20about%20any%20marginalised%20community%20that%20feels%20unheard.%E2%80%9D%20Reporters%20treat%20the%20magazine%20as%20their%20own%20constitution%2C%20and%20Naseema%20encourages%20them%20to%20share%20it%20with%20others.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20people%20pay%20you%20the%20support%20funds%2C%20great.%20If%20not%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20never%20a%20waste.%20It%20will%20at%20least%20make%20them%20realise%20that%20you%20are%20a%20reporter%20or%20writer%2C%20someone%20powerful.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202023%2C%20Naseema%20also%20started%20a%20pioneering%20initiative%2C%20called%20Police%20Paathshaala%2C%20in%20her%20hometown.%20The%20programme%20aims%20to%20change%20the%20way%20children%20of%20Chaturbhuj%20Sthan%20engage%20with%20the%20police.%20Officers%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F330978%2Fkamlesh-atwal-started-nanakmatta-public-school-uttarakhand-holistic-education-for-students%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteach%20the%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20play%20with%20them%2C%20and%20even%20bring%20them%20cakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaseema%20reflects%20on%20the%20stark%20contrast%20between%20her%20childhood%20and%20what%20these%20children%20experience%20today.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20was%20little%2C%20I%20was%20always%20told%20to%20hide%20from%20the%20police%2C%20to%20fear%20them.%20But%20these%20kids%3F%20You%20should%20see%20them%20jump%20around%20and%20boss%20the%20officers%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20quite%20funny!%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201040px)%20100vw%2C%201040px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu2-1733397861.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221040%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Local%20police%20officers%20engage%20with%20children%20in%20a%20friendly%20and%20open%20environment.%20The%20scene%20conveys%20a%20sense%20of%20trust%20and%20comfort%2C%20with%20the%20children%20feeling%20at%20ease%2C%20building%20positive%20relationships%20with%20the%20officers.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu2-1733397861.jpg%201040w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu2-1733397861-300x135.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu2-1733397861-500x225.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu2-1733397861-768x346.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2Fjugnu2-1733397861-150x68.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-386779%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22468%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20local%20police%20officers%20and%20children%20regularly%20interact%20in%20a%20positive%20environment%2C%20creating%20a%20sense%20of%20trust%20and%20security%20among%20the%20kids%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20programme%20began%20in%20a%20spare%20police%20room%20that%20was%20going%20to%20waste%20and%20has%20since%20grown%20from%2015%20children%20to%20over%20100.%20Many%20of%20these%20children%2C%20like%20Naseema%20once%20was%2C%20are%20school%20dropouts%20who%20face%20societal%20stigma.%20Yet%2C%20they%20proudly%20identify%20themselves%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20kids%20of%20Police%20Paathshaala%E2%80%9D.%20Arif%2C%20with%20his%20dreams%20of%20being%20a%20police%20officer%20still%20intact%2C%20closely%20works%20with%20these%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20regulatory%20hurdles%2C%20the%20goal%20remains%20to%20make%20the%20magazine%20profitable%2C%20so%20the%20children%20involved%20can%20benefit%20from%20the%20funds%20raised.%20For%20now%2C%20reporters%20receive%20copies%20of%20the%20magazine%20and%20keep%20whatever%20support%20funds%20they%20can%20collect%20from%20distributing%20them.%20Financial%20support%20from%20donors%2C%20such%20as%20the%20MG%20Charitable%20Trust%20in%20the%20US%2C%20has%20been%20crucial%20in%20printing%20the%20magazine%2C%20with%20the%20first%20100%20copies%20printed%20in%202021%20thanks%20to%20their%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20want%20to%20see%20change%2C%20work%20for%20these%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20they%20are%20the%20future%2C%E2%80%9D%20Naseema%20says.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20Prem%20becomes%20somebody%2C%20and%20he%20will%2C%20he%E2%80%99ll%20carry%20this%20goodness%20forward.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Arunava%20Banerjee%3B%20Images%20courtesy%20Naseema%20Khatoon%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733715000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D386658%22%2C